All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    EquationsSimplifier
    A program used to demonstrate the usage of the Matrix class to simplify systems equations, it also tells the user how many solutions a system of equations has.
    LinearDependence
    A program used to demonstrate the usage of the Matrix class to check if a set of vectors are linearly independent.
    MarkovChains
    A program used to demonstrate the usage of the Matrix class to perform Markov chains.
    Matrix
    A class representing a Matrix, the operations that can either be used by a Matrix or on a Matrix, and the different forms or decompositions that a Matrix can have.
    MatrixTools
    A class that provides static methods for performing matrix operations, similar to the default Math class While using static methods does not follow OOP conventions, it provides a way for people only familiar with procedural programming to work with the Matrix class in a friendlier and more intuitive way.
    Span
    A program used to demonstrate the usage of the Matrix class to check if w is in the span of a set of vectors.
    Tester
    A program used to demonstrate the usage of the Matrix class to perform many different matrix operations.
